# Subject: 50 chars max, no period at end, imperative mood
# Example: feat(api): add a new endpoint

# Body: 72 chars max per line. Explain 'what' and 'why' (not 'how').
# Multiple paragraphs are allowed, separated by a blank line.

# Footer: Optional metadata like issue references or breaking changes.
# Example: Closes #123
# Example: BREAKING CHANGE: <description>

# feat: A new feature.
# fix: A bug fix.
# docs: Documentation only changes.
# style: Changes that do not affect code logic (whitespace, formatting, etc.).
# refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.
# perf: A code change that improves performance.
# test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests.
# build: Changes that affect build components or dependencies.
# chore: Miscellaneous tasks or maintenance commits (e.g., modifying .gitignore).
# ops: Operational changes (infrastructure, deployment, CI/CD).
